page.title: 13Bryan Gould M.P.
page.content: Bryan Gould is a gregarious 46 year old New Zealander, married with a son and two daughters. He came to Russells Water in 1979 near to where his ancestor, Caleb Gould, had been legendary lock-keeper at Hambledon. At the start of his career, he read law at Aukland University N.Z. and was a Rhodes Scholar at Baliol, Oxford. In 1964 he joined the Diplomatic Service for two years at the Foreign Office and two years at the Brussel's Embassy. In 1968 he became Fellow and Tutor at Worcester College. He became Labour M.P.for Southampton Test in 1974, losing his seat in 1979; he became a T.V.journalist. In 1983 he returned to Parliament as M.P. for Dagenham. He is now Shadow spokes- man for Trade. His hobbies are food, wine and gardening.
